      <title>eZOracle 1.8.3 released</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezoracle/news/ezoracle_1_8_3_released</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The latest bugfix release for eZ Publish versions 4.0.x is out, with over a year worth of changes - too many to list here.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Notable changes include:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
- vastly improved the consistency checks and the generated corrective sql in the "Setup"/"System upgrade check" page&lt;br /&gt;
 To take full advantage of the improvements, you should use eZ Publish 4.0.8+&lt;br /&gt;
 For lower versions in the 4.0 series a patched kernel/setup/systemupgrade.php script&lt;br /&gt; is available in the 'patches' directory of the extension.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
- new parameters are possible to improve performance of the index_image_oracle.php&lt;br /&gt; script in cluster setups. More details in the README.cluster file&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Gaetano Giunta)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ezoracle/news/ezoracle_1_8_3_released</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 17 Oct 2010 20:30:58 +0000</pubDate>
