    <item>
      <title>eZ Oracle 2.0.1 released</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezoracle/news/ez_oracle_2_0_1_released</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The latest version of the "eZ Publish database extension for Oracle", also known as eZ Oracle,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;

&lt;li&gt;adds the upgrade script for eZ Publish up to 4.1.3&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;corrects a couple of bugs, one of which prevented the installation using 'fully manual' mode&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Please note:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;the mechanism used to derive the names of sequences for tables that are created by extensions has been changed in this release (sequences are the oracle-equivalent of self-incrementing fields in mysql). Take care if you are upgrading from a previous version and have installed any extension that uses persistent objects based on custom tables.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Gaetano Giunta)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ezoracle/news/ez_oracle_2_0_1_released</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 30 Jun 2009 12:51:26 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
