    <item>
      <title>eZ Oracle 1.6, 1.7 and 1.8 released</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezoracle/news/ez_oracle_1_6_1_7_and_1_8_released</link>
      <description> &lt;p&gt;I am happy to announce the eZ Oracle Christmas Release!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After more than a year of work, versions of the extension corresponding to eZ Publish 3.9, 3.10 and 4.0 are finally generally available.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Lots of bugs have been fixed and performance has been tweaked to a great extent, too.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Please make sure to read with care the release notes and install/upgrade instructions that come with each version.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;In particular:&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt;
 
&lt;li&gt; eZ Oracle 1.6 is considered a stop-gap measure, as there are known bugs in eZ Publish 3.9.5 running on Oracle, and version 3.9.6 has not been released (it will most likely never be). Please upgrade at least to eZ Publish 3.10.1 if you plan to use an Oracle database with eZ Publish 3. &lt;/li&gt;
 
&lt;li&gt; The "eZ Publish clustering" mode requires some patches to the eZ Publish kernel files for versions 3.10.1 and 4.0.1. All the relevant patches are included within the eZ Oracle extension &lt;/li&gt;
 
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Gaetano Giunta)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ezoracle/news/ez_oracle_1_6_1_7_and_1_8_released</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 22 Dec 2008 15:48:25 +0000</pubDate>
